Padoan's gloss (comm. to ^Inf~. IV.73) on Dante's phrase is
worth noting: ^sc&#962;enz&#962;a~ ('knowledge') is represented by
philosophy and the seven liberal arts, while ^arte~ ('art' in a more
restricted sense than is found in the modern term) has to do with the
means of expressing knowledge.
