..TEXT:
Virgil is not suggesting that his fellow ancient poets do well
to praise him, but that in praising him they honor their shared
profession.  If there is a 'humanistic' gesture in this canto, we find
it here, 'a solemn celebration of the worth of poetry' (see Padoan,
comm. to ^Inf~. IV.93).
